  "title": "Senior Accounting Executive/Assistant Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>About Company:</strong></p><p>Our client was incorporated in 2016. It is a professional services firm that provides tax, accounting, and business consulting services to local and international clients operating in Singapore and across Southeast Asia. Their business encompasses a range of services, including cross-border business structuring, M&A advisory, regional expansion strategies, and transfer pricing matters, among others.</p><p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><p>- Conducting Financial Due Diligence (FDD)</p><p>- Prepare month-end closing and annual financial statements for clients</p><p>- Ensure firm's service standards and reporting deadlines are met</p><p>- Liaise with clients, auditors, and tax agents on accounting, audit and taxation matters</p><p>- Other ad hoc duties as assigned by the company</p><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><p>- At least 3 years of experience in a professional audit and accounting firm, or having experience of performing FDD</p><p>- Familiarity with Singapore Financial Reporting Standards (SFRS)</p><p>- Independent, organized, and able to work collaboratively with colleagues</p><p>- Basic proficiency in Microsoft Excel and Word</p><p>- Willing to travel overseas, including Malaysia, Indonesia, and the Philippines for some projects purposes</p><p>- Basic knowledge and experience of tax computation</p><p><strong>Compensation:</strong></p><p>- Working location: CBD, Singapore</p><p>- Working hours: Monday to Friday (9am - 6pm)</p><p>- AWS Entitlement and Performance bonus</p><p>- Annual leave and medical leave</p><p>- Medical benefits up to $1,000 annually</p><p>- A career opportunity to work alongside accounting and taxation professionals</p><p>- Overseas business trips opportunity with diverse working culture</p><p>- Career progression opportunity<a href=\"https://www.jointhire.com.sg/job/3556?utm_source=followup\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"></a></p>",
